==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Alb
<hw>Alb</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>albe</ets>,
LL. <ets>alba</ets>, fr. L. <ets>albus</ets> white. Cf. <er>Album</er>
and <er>Aube</er>.]</ety> <def>A vestment of white linen, reaching to
the feet, an enveloping the person; -- in the Roman Catholic church,
worn by those in holy orders when officiating at mass. It was formerly
worn, at least by clerics, in daily life.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Albacore</ent>⟦br⟧
